		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Hello! I'm working on a plugin to quickly turn any (block based) button into a Freemius Checkout button. Here's a test to purchase my plugin (Mailster): </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:buttons -->
<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"freemius_enabled":true} -->
<div class="wp-block-button has-freemius-checkout"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button">Buy Mailster Now</a></div>
<!-- /wp:button --></div>
<!-- /wp:buttons -->

<!-- wp:buttons -->
<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"freemius_enabled":true,"freemius":{"plan_id":"22866"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-button has-freemius-checkout"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button">Starter</a></div>
<!-- /wp:button -->

<!-- wp:button {"freemius_enabled":true,"freemius":{"plan_id":"22867"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-button has-freemius-checkout"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button">Professional</a></div>
<!-- /wp:button -->

<!-- wp:button {"freemius_enabled":true,"freemius":{"plan_id":"22868"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-button has-freemius-checkout"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button">Agency</a></div>
<!-- /wp:button --></div>
<!-- /wp:buttons -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The button provides basically (almost) all options from the <a href="https://freemius.com/help/documentation/selling-with-freemius/freemius-checkout-buy-button/">offical docs</a>. Just click on the button and enable the "<em>Freemius Checkout </em>" checkbox.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>My goal is to make it easy to create checkout button if you sell on Freemius.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>You need at least two properties</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>product_id</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>public_key</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>All other options are optional but please check the <a href="https://freemius.com/help/documentation/selling-with-freemius/freemius-checkout-buy-button/">offical docs</a>.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Scopes</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Freemius Button can work with three scopes: Global, Page and Button. This way you can define settings for your whole site/page which can get overwritten specifically.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The "Button" scope overwrites settings from "Page" which overwrites settings from "Global"</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Global</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The global scope stores the value in the <code>wp_options</code> table. Data can be used across your whole site.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Page</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This scope is for the current page. It is stored in the <code>post_meta</code> table and is valid for the current page only. It inherits the Global settings.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Button</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>These is for individual buttons. The data is stored in the block attributes. It inherits data from the Page settings as well the Global settings.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Filters</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I've added a filter you can use to change the arguments on-the file which works something like that:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:preformatted -->
<pre class="wp-block-preformatted">add_filter('freemius_button_data', function($data) {<br>	$data['plan_id'] = 456;<br>	return $data;<br>});</pre>
<!-- /wp:preformatted -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading">More Examples</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:buttons -->
<div class="wp-block-buttons"><!-- wp:button {"className":"has-freemius-checkout","freemius_enabled":true,"freemius":{"trial":true}} -->
<div class="wp-block-button has-freemius-checkout has-freemius-checkout"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button">Start a Trial</a></div>
<!-- /wp:button -->

<!-- wp:button {"freemius_enabled":true,"freemius":{"trial":true,"plan_id":"22868"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-button has-freemius-checkout"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button">Start a Trial of a different Plan</a></div>
<!-- /wp:button -->

<!-- wp:button {"freemius_enabled":true,"freemius":{"plan_id":"22868","coupon":"WPTESTER"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-button has-freemius-checkout"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button">Apply Coupon</a></div>
<!-- /wp:button -->

<!-- wp:button {"freemius_enabled":true,"freemius":{"plan_id":"22868","coupon":"WPTESTER","hide_coupon":true}} -->
<div class="wp-block-button has-freemius-checkout"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button">Apply Coupon (hidden)</a></div>
<!-- /wp:button -->

<!-- wp:button {"freemius_enabled":true,"freemius":{"plan_id":"22868","track":"console.log('Event triggered: ' + event)"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-button has-freemius-checkout"><a class="wp-block-button__link wp-element-button">Run some events (check console)</a></div>
<!-- /wp:button --></div>
<!-- /wp:buttons -->
]]></content:encoded>
